This folder contains the addons and modifications made in top of Tarek Galal's Yowsup API
in order to interface correctly with the web services at http://www.WhatsAppVoyeur.com, 
which have been designed to parse XML outputs

TOOLS AND USAGE
===============

* syncparser.py and ../whatsappcontactquery.py

parser from default non-formatted response of yowsup contact sync v2 API to XML friendly format

the parser code is in syncparser.py while whatsappcontactquery acts as an example interface
whatsappcontactquery.py is just a clone of original yowsup-cli with small modifications in order to be 100% quiet so it does not mess up the XML output to standard output.

whatsappcontactquery.py usage:

identical to yowsup-cli:
python whatsappcontactquery.py --sync number,number2,number3,...

syncparser.py usage in your code:
    
    contacts = args["sync"].split(',')
    wsync = WAContactsSyncRequest(login, password, contacts)
		result = wsync.send()
		xmlOutput = parseSyncOutput2XML(resultToString(result))

and use xmlOutput like you want 

example output:

python whatsappqueryv2.py --sync 650000000,650000001,650000002
<contact>
<p>650000002</p>
<s>Hey there! I am using WhatsApp.</s>
<t>1357862643</t>
<w>1</w>
<n>34650000002</n>
</contact>
<contact>
<p>650000000</p>
<s>\ue525\ue531\ue10b\ue528\ue52d\ue523\ue52e</s>
<t>1343500992</t>
<w>1</w>
<n>34650000000</n>
</contact>
<contact>
<p>650000001</p>
<w>0</w>
<n>34650000001</n>
</contact>
